      • isReal

        public boolean isReal()
        Is equivalent to instanceof RealLookupElementPresentation check.
        Returns:
        whether the presentation is requested to actually render lookup element on screen, or just to estimate its width. In the second, 'non-real' case, some heavy operations (e.g. getIcon()) can be omitted (only icon width is important)
